  "canonical_definition": "Cogalent pruning is a procedure that removes elements from a structure not by individual importance score but by joint redundancy across paired elements, retaining one member of each co-redundant pair and dropping the other, distinguishing it from magnitude pruning (importance-driven) and from structured pruning (geometry-driven).",
